{
  "stem": "11067.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There I was-- we were to meet at the station, my father and my sister, to say goodbye.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Only one parent, one guardian-- parent, guardian, whatever-- was allowed to go with you to the transport train.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We reached Worms, and there-- as I say, I can-- I think I can see it as clear as it had happened yesterday-- were my father and my sister at the railway station.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we said goodbye.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then, we, my mother and I, went further to the town of Mainz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Now, there was another thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We had not been able to get Dramamine for the sea journey for me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "No one would sell it to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So you know, there was another thing of, of, of the anti-Semitism, of the dirty Jew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My mother did buy me a pen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I remember distinctly it was a pelican pen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it was encased in a little leather tube case [INAUDIBLE] and put that into my bag.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And the train pulled in at Mainz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That was my transport train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "There probably were 400 or 500 on that train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Only for Jewish kids.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Only for Jewish kids from the age of babies to 18.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The train pulled in, and that's the first time that I saw my mother flinch.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first two cars of my train were babies in hammocks.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were people there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were women, apparently.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was somebody in a white uniform.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know who or what they were, I suppose watching over these.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we do-- I do remember seeing those first two railway cars with hammocks and babies in them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother saw that, and that was the first time in all those horrible months that I saw her flinch.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
